<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicom disk system strap slipping and jamming]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4941&amp;p=44127#p44127"><![CDATA[
I received from my brother in law in Japan a while ago a broken Famicom disk system.  After opening it, the problem was the usual one: a melted strap.<br /><br />I was able to find in Akihabara a new strap, followed the instruction from a website on the net (I think it was this <a href="http://www.pinkgodzillagames.com/retro_reviews/simply_ness_guide_to_famicom_d.php" class="postlink">one</a>) and it seemed to work. Games were booting and everything.  The only problem is that once in a while, the strap start to slip and jam. So you have to re-open the unit and put back the strap in place.<br /><br />Does anybody had this issue before?  I'm not sure if I missed something in the procedure or the strap could be the issue.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3559">Banshaku</a> â€” Tue Mar 10, 2009 11:51 pm</p><hr />
